reviews.review_text:
- Low side of 5 stars, as the recording is excellent, and so is everything before drums (even the terribly rushed Eyes is played with refreshing inventiveness). It's the most boring Drums I've ever heard, and second set part 2 isn't as good as the rest, but the rest makes up. Unbelievable Desolation Row.

Just shows how your ears can grow over time. By spring '87 standards, this is actually a real sucker.
